The paper deals with generative adversarial networks (GANs) for facial semantic inpainting, which involves filling in missing parts of an image. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses optimization techniques and recurrent neural networks, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions temporal smoothness and sequence inpainting, which are related to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
